# Example environment configuration for surrogate_models.
#
# Copy to `.env` and adjust (the real `.env` is gitignored). Variables are
# prefixed SURROGATE_MODELS__ and nest into config sections with the same `__`
# delimiter, so SURROGATE_MODELS__DATASETS__PATH sets the datasets section's
# `path`. Precedence, highest first: OS env / .env, then surrogate_models.toml,
# then the built-in defaults.
#
# Paths must be ABSOLUTE (config rejects a relative value). The built-in defaults
# are filesystem-rooted, so they resolve the same from any working directory --
# including a notebook under notebooks/. The values below mirror those defaults;
# change them to your machine's actual locations. `.env` expands ${VAR} from the
# environment, so a repo-local override can use ${HOME}
# (e.g. ${HOME}/projects/surrogate_models/data/neutron-stars/neutron-stars.dat);
# `~` does NOT expand in any source, and NOTHING expands in surrogate_models.toml.

# Where the datasets bounded context persists datasets (parquet).
SURROGATE_MODELS__DATASETS__PATH=/var/data/surrogate_models/datasets

# Raw concatenated neutron-stars .dat file the ingest reader digests.
SURROGATE_MODELS__DATASETS__NEUTRON_STARS_SOURCE=/data/neutron-stars/neutron-stars.dat
